{"title":"Standards compliant","link":"https://www.adamkoch.com/2008/06/12/standards-compliant/","pubDate":"Thu, 12 Jun 2008 14:05:14 +0000","dc:creator":"admin","guid":[{"_":"http://www.myrantsite.com/2008/06/12/standards-compliant/","$":{"isPermaLink":"false"}}],"description":[""],"content:encoded":"I used to be all for standards compliance and added links like <a href=\"http://validator.w3.org/check?uri=referer\">this</a> to my site, but then you come back a month later and your site is no longer valid. So I stopped doing it.\n\nSo this amused me: <a title=\"Plogger homepage\" href=\"http://www.plogger.org/\">Plogger</a> states on the bottom of their home page \"Plogger produces <a href=\"http://validator.w3.org/check?uri=referer\">fully validated</a> XHTML 1.1 code\", but it's <a href=\"http://validator.w3.org/check?uri=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.plogger.org%2F\">not</a>. <img src=\"http://dogtired.org/images/smilies/lol14.gif\" alt=\"laughing smilie\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" /> Not a good way to promote your product!\n\nHmm... I wonder if there's a site that lists sites like this, just to make fun of them.","excerpt:encoded":"","wp:post_id":"1089","wp:post_date":"2008-06-12 09:05:14","wp:post_date_gmt":"2008-06-12 14:05:14","wp:post_modified":["2008-06-12 09:05:14"],"wp:post_modified_gmt":["2008-06-12 14:05:14"],"wp:comment_status":["open"],"wp:ping_status":["open"],"wp:post_name":"standards-compliant","wp:status":"publish","wp:post_parent":["0"],"wp:menu_order":["0"],"wp:post_type":"post","wp:post_password":[""],"wp:is_sticky":["0"],"category":[{"_":"Professional","$":{"domain":"category","nicename":"professional"}}],"wp:postmeta":[{"wp:meta_key":["_utw_tags_0"],"wp:meta_value":["no tags"]},{"wp:meta_key":["aktt_tweeted"],"wp:meta_value":["1"]},{"wp:meta_key":["_edit_last"],"wp:meta_value":["1"]},{"wp:meta_key":["_jetpack_related_posts_cache"],"wp:meta_value":["a:1:{s:32:\"37550b67d263a3ce789993dc25046c5f\";a:2:{s:7:\"expires\";i:1627497065;s:7:\"payload\";a:6:{i:0;a